<br>
Oh Hades, I love you so much, more than anyone I've ever known. When I saw you standing outside of your body, I nearly lost my mind. I do not mean to yell, its just that sometimes I become so miserable and I say things that I do not mean. Just hold me here until I fall asleep..please..<br>
<br>
::With that, Persephone closes her eyes and snuggles up to her husband. After a few minutes, tiny, soft snores begin to purr from her sweet lips:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ixlordhadesxi>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 264<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/16/03 3:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=78>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Seeking answer</span><hr size=1> ::Hades lied there quietly until Persephone fell asleep. Rather than disturb her by moving, he melded into a shadow and reappeared at the doorway. He blew her a kiss and walked out of the room allowing her to sleep soundly::<br>
